.TH AXT-OUTLINE 1 "2026-04-28" "axt 0.1.0-rc1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
axt-outline \- emit compact source outlines without function bodies
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B axt-outline
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIPATH\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B axt-outline
prints declarations, signatures, doc comments, symbol kinds, visibility,
file paths, and source ranges. Function bodies are not emitted.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --json
Emit an axt.outline.v1 JSON envelope.
.TP
.B --json-data
Emit only the JSON data payload.
.TP
.B --jsonl
Emit newline-delimited JSON records.
.TP
.B --agent
Emit Agent Compact Format.
.TP
.B --plain
Emit plain human output.
.TP
.B --public-only
Emit only public, crate-visible, and restricted symbols.
.TP
.B --lang rust|typescript|javascript|python|go|java|php
Select one supported language.
.TP
.B --max-depth N
Maximum directory traversal depth.
.TP
.B --sort path|name|kind|source
Select output ordering.
.TP
.B --limit N
Maximum line-oriented output records.
.TP
.B --max-bytes BYTES
Maximum line-oriented output bytes.
.TP
.B --strict
Exit non-zero if truncation is required.
.TP
.B --print-schema [FORMAT]
Print schema information and exit.
.TP
.B --list-errors
Print the standard error catalog and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
0
Success.
.TP
3
Input path not found.
.TP
6
Output truncated under --strict.
.TP
8
Filesystem or output error.
.TP
9
No supported source files were found.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR axt-peek (1),
.BR axt-test (1)
